    q: "What does 'vertical-specific' web design actually mean?",
    a: "Three things change by industry: the schema type Google needs to classify your business correctly, the compliance rules that govern what you can say and how, and the conversion architecture that matches how your customer decides to act. A dental site needs Dentist schema and online booking. A law firm site needs LegalService schema and MRPC-compliant copy. A contractor site needs HomeAndConstructionBusiness schema and multi-step estimate forms. A generalist agency delivers none of these correctly.",
